Chapter Objectives Last updated Save as PDF Page ID Contributors and Attributions After you have completed Chapter you should be able to fulfill the detailed objectives listed under each section identify some of the commonest functional groups write the structures and names of the first ten straightchain alkanes recognize and name the simple alkyl substituents and give the systematic names for branchedchain alkanes briefly describe some of the processes used during the refining of petroleum briefly describe the physical properties of alkanes draw a number of possible conformations of some simple alkanes and alkanelike compounds and represent the energies of such conformations on energy versus rotation diagrams define and use in context the key terms introduced in this chapter Contributors and Attributions Dr Dietmar Kennepohl FCIC Professor of Chemistry Athabasca University